      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_Published_EstimatedMeterReadings_Upgrade",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to generate a report of estimated meter readings for a specified billing period. It logs the report usage and retrieves data from the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Published.TemporalAccountMeterLevelRawDataForCurrentPeriod",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " table, filtering based on agency codes and other criteria. The procedure is part of a reporting system, likely used by agencies to monitor utility meter readings that have been estimated for consecutive periods."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure involves conditional logic, dynamic SQL execution, and joins across multiple tables. It also includes logging functionality and handles different scenarios based on user roles and agency codes. The complexity arises from the conditional logic and the need to handle different user roles and agency codes."
        }
      ]
    },
